section.section:
The Commissioner shall approve a name, trademark, or emblem if the name, trademark, or emblem:
is distinctive;
is not similar to or in conflict with the name, trademark, or emblem of a local organization or a nationally registered or copyrighted name, trademark, or emblem;
is not likely to confuse or mislead the public about the nature or identity of the applicant or licensee using or proposing to use the name, trademark, or emblem; and
will not interfere with the transactions of a licensee already operating in the State.
